<DOC><DOCNO> AP890305-0021 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-05-89 1153EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-Eastern-CommuterRailroads     03-05 0151</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Eastern-Commuter Railroads,0162</SECOND><HEAD>Railroads Governed by the Railway Labor Act</HEAD><HEAD>With AM-Eastern Bjt</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Here is a list of the 12 commuter railroadsgoverned by the federal Railway Labor Act, and therefore vulnerableto secondary boycotts from the Eastern Machinists union strike,which entered its second day Sunday. The list was provided by theAmerican Public Transit Association.   _Massachuetts Bay Transportation Authority in Boston.   _Northern Indiana Commuter Transportation District.   _Maryland Transportation Authority of Baltimore and suburbanWashington.   _Metro-North Commuter Rail Road, serving New York City suburbs.   _Long Island Rail Road, serving New York City suburbs.   _New Jersey Transit.   _PATH, Port Authority Trans-Hudson rail system, in New York andNew Jersey.   _SEPTA, Southeast Pennsylvania Transportation Authority, ofPhiladelphia.   _METRA, Rapid Transportation Authority in Chicago.   _CalTrans, which operates between San Fransisco and San Jose.   _PAT, the Port Authority of Alleghany County, Pittsburgh.   _Tri-Rail, South Florida's new 67-mile rail system.</TEXT></DOC>